“How is it?” you wonder.
Singaporeans are laughing.
Everything happens.
Not for every such "crime" will be caught on the spot, but you must know: if you are calculated, you will not retaliate - because you have violated the law.
Most often this is enough for a person to behave normally.
Of course, the power in Singapore is quite authoritarian.
But you know what?
In Ho Chi Minh, Vietnam, I moved very carefully – motorcyclists often pick up smartphones and cameras from the hands of tourists.
The centre of Paris is full of dirty bombs and beggars.
On our streets, too, not everyone tries to throw rubbish into urns.
Singapore, thanks to a set of draconian fines and ruthless (up to the death penalty) laws, has become the most peaceful, clean and safe city on Earth.
You will think.
