The order and place of the oath shall be determined by the President.
Where and how new Russian citizens will swear allegiance to the Russian Federation, will be determined by the president - such amendments to the second reading of the relevant law developed by the State Duma committee on legislation and state construction.
A week ago, the deputies planned to directly determine the procedure for sworn-in in the law.
Children under the age of 18 will be released from the solemn oath, as well as those who are incapable, according to the amendments to the draft law "On citizenship of the Russian Federation" (is at the disposal of "Izvestia"), which the committee will consider before the second reading on its meeting on July 11.
The idea of introducing an oath when obtaining Russian citizenship instead of formal signing documents was supported by President Vladimir Putin on June 6 during a meeting with the Speaker of the State Duma Vyacheslav Volodin.
Deputies formed this idea in the form of an amendment to the second reading of the bill, which provides for the abolition of the decision on granting citizenship to those who were subsequently convicted for a number of crimes of a terrorist or extremist nature: for example, for public appeals to terrorism or its public justification in the media or on the Internet (Article 2 of Article 205.2 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation), as well as for the kidnapping of a plane, train or water transport, but only if this act is connected with terrorism (Article 4 of Article 211 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation).
According to the bill, its logic was this: when issuing documents for citizenship, a person signs under a promise to comply with the Russian legislation - taking the path of extremism, he breaks this promise.
The bill was submitted to the State Duma in April by the leaders of the Duma factions Vladimir Vasilyev (“United Russia”), Gennady Zyuganov (KPRF), Vladimir Zhirinovsky (LDPR), Sergey Mironov (“Fair Russia”) and the speaker of the DG Vyacheslav Volodin.
On May 19, the deputies adopted it in the first reading.
Last week, the DG Committee on State Construction and Legislation approved the text of the bill for second reading, but now it has been revised again.
The order of the oath will be established by the President of the Russian Federation.
Earlier, parliamentarians planned to describe the procedure directly in the law "On citizenship of the Russian Federation", stating that the ceremony should take place in a solemn setting in front of the state emblem and flag of Russia in the presence of a representative of the Ministry of Internal Affairs.
However, it was not clear from the text of the bill where such an event should take place - the list of places where the emblem of the Russian Federation can be placed is regulated by the corresponding federal constitutional law.
They include courts, cabinets of heads of state bodies of subjects, municipalities, judges, prosecutors, heads of federal executive bodies, etc.
Probably, it could also be cracks.
Those who wish to obtain Russian citizenship will take a solemn oath after officials check their documents.
But the Russian passport will only be obtained after the oath, it follows from the revised text.
A week ago, the draft stated that the oath must precede the signing of the decree.
Russia will be sworn in at the age of 18, not at the age of 14.
It is preserved that those who are incapable or limited in capacity, as well as those who cannot pronounce, read or sign the text of the oath, will be released from taking the oath.
In addition, the President of the Russian Federation has the right to exempt "other persons" from this procedure.
Also in the updated bill prescribed a special procedure for admission in Russian citizens of residents of Ukraine, who are considered natives of the Russian language.
They will have to officially give up Ukrainian citizenship by submitting a corresponding application to the authorized body of Ukraine.
A notarially certified copy of the application will need to be handed over to Russian officials.
A renunciation of “foreign” citizenship, as is now the case, will not be required if it is provided for by an international treaty or if it is not possible “for reasons beyond the person”.
The corresponding amendment to the law was proposed by a group of deputies, among them the first deputy speaker of the DG Ivan Melnikov (KPRF), Natalia Poklonskaya, Pavel Krasheninnikov and Ayrat Farrahov (all - "United Russia").
I think many of you know that getting a certificate from Ukraine is unrealistic, it is simply impossible.
Accordingly, a lot of people are waiting for a decision on their fate regarding the citizenship of the Russian Federation, - explained the head of the Duma Committee on State Construction and Legislation Pavel Krasheninnikov (ER).
In addition, the text clarified that the restrictions on the occupation of certain positions for foreigners will not apply to those who have written renounced "other" citizenship and handed down the previous passport to the Ministry of Internal Affairs of Russia, but "for reasons not dependent on him" he did not cease to be considered a citizen of another country.
Foreigners are now prohibited from holding positions in the municipal service, being employed in facilities and in organizations whose activities are related to ensuring the security of Russia.
Also, a person with dual citizenship or residence permit of another country cannot become a deputy of the State Duma or a member of the Federation Council.
It is planned that the law should enter into force from 1 September 2017, by that time the necessary legal acts should be prepared.
