The Gypsies overcame the river and returned to the "millionaire street"
Some of West Midland’s wealthiest homeowners are once again in conflict with the determined Gypsies who have overcome the municipality’s river to re-occupy the field next to their homes.
The Gypsies parked 20 houses on wheels in a field bordering the rich street Solihalla, which was jokingly called "millionaire street".
Having brought with them horses, babies and many houses on wheels, they returned after being expelled no later than in May, and they were not hindered by a pit excavated by the municipal authorities to prevent their invasion.
This tactical company found a gap in the defensive structures and dragged its vehicles through the site, which was left unfocused to leave room for the trail.
Angry residents attacked the municipality of Solihalla, saying it was “unable to solve the problem.”
An anonymous local resident said: “They came here on Monday evening after being driven out of Bentley Heath, where they were throwing stones at passers.”
The municipality should be ashamed and forced to act, because they are absolutely incapable of solving this problem.
The Gypsies were here in May, they were expelled, and here they came back again.
More Roma came last night, and maybe even more today.
“The Birmingham municipality knows how to solve this problem, they are getting long-term court orders to protect their parks,” she added.
“I live on the street and I don’t like that I’m still paying municipal taxes, and the municipality can’t even end it.”
One local resident, who wanted to remain anonymous, said: “It’s funny, we just saw these Gypsies leave the last time, and please, this attack continues.”
This time they became more, and we even saw a horse riding on the lawn.”
A spokesman for the municipality of Solihalla said: “We are aware of the illegal camp on the ground near the Street Street Road and we are cooperating with Solihalla police; we are taking the necessary legal action to evacuate them as soon as possible.”
To help us collect evidence, it is very important that as many locals as possible report any antisocial or criminal behavior to the police by phone 101.
This allows us to make an idea of the situation that the court will consider when we present our case to them.
Crimea to activate champagne wine factory "New World"
GUP of the Republic of Crimea "Fabric of Champagne Wines "New World" is decided to share, transforming into the OJSC "Fabric of Champagne Wines "New World"", follows from the order of the Minister of Property and Land Relations of Crimea Anna Anjukhina.
100% of the shares of the company will remain in state ownership of Crimea.
