Andrei Ohlopkov moved from the cosmodrome
As it became known "Ъ", the technical director of the cosmodrome East Andrei Ohlopkov began work in the State Space Scientific and Production Center (GKNPC) named Khrunichev.
Earlier, he de facto engaged in the construction of the cosmodrome Vostochny, but due to disagreements with the management of the Center for the operation of ground and space infrastructure (CENKI) was transferred to the enterprise in Moscow's Files, where he will coordinate production.
Mr. Ohlopkov will not have a substitute: the position of the technical director will most likely be abolished, and the functionality will be scattered by the units of CENKI.
About the fact that Technical Director of the East and Deputy Director General of the Central Energy Agency for Technological Development Andrei Ohlopkov went to work in the Khrunichev GKNPC, "Ъ" told top managers of several enterprises of the space industry, as well as an employee of the government apparatus.
"He has been working on the new post for several weeks," the industry's interlocutors said.
It was not possible to obtain an operational comment from CENKI on Thursday, and Mr. Ohlopkov himself was unavailable for comments.
However, the information "Ъ" was officially confirmed in GKNPC.
He decided to move to the position of director for coordination of production, - said at the enterprise. - Andrei Ohlopkov has fully fulfilled the task set before him to ensure the launch minimum for the first launch at the cosmodrome Vostochny.
Mr. Ohlopkov moved to work at CENKI in 2013, having behind his shoulders service in the space troops, in particular at Baikonur, and in Plesetsk - at the "northern" cosmodrome he held the post of first deputy commander in the rank of colonel.
In 2009, Andrey Ohlopkov became a figure in a criminal case.
The investigation accused him of bribery: allegedly, from his submission, regional merchants received state orders for scooters, but did not fulfill their commitments on cleaning the separable parts of carriers in the Arkhangelsk region and the Republic of Komi.
In 2012, the jury found him innocent.
The duties on technological development assigned to him in the CENKI extended to various projects, but the main of them was the construction of a cosmodrome in the Far East.
Oleg Ostapenko, then head of the Federal Space Agency, in an interview with "Ъ" directly said that the situation on the East "was critical already in October 2013".
The fact is that a strategic mistake was made in planning: the completion of construction and the first launch of the Soyuz-2.1 carrier missile were planned for the same time - the end of 2015.
In order to launch before the end of the year, the construction was decided to be completed six months earlier and the deadline was moved from December to July 2015.
To speed up the process, we had to go to the trick: CENKI specialists began to conduct parallel installation of technological equipment on unbuilt facilities.
The main proponent of this idea was Andrey Ohlopkov.
Despite the existing risks and yet the transfer that happened (instead of December 2015 "Soyuz" flew only April 28, 2016), this idea was justified, says the source "Ъ" at the cosmodrome: "Otherwise we would not have yet carried out a single launch from the Eastern, but would be engaged in construction."
Deputy Prime Minister Dmitry Rogozin, who oversaw the creation of the cosmodrome, jokingly called Andrei Ohlopkov his "space Susanin", but it was from him that he almost always asked for information about the progress of construction.
Mr. Ohlopkov also remembered the straightforwardness: for example, in an interview with "Ъ" he proposed to deprive the Federal Agency for Special Construction (Specstroy) of the status of the only executor on the Eastern and directly work with subcontractors: "Why should we put all the eggs in one basket of the Special Construction?"
This idea has been supported by the government.
Since 2017, CENKI has assumed the duties of a general contractor to complete construction and installation work on the start and technical complex to the planned launch in the fourth quarter.
According to "Ъ", the reason for the transfer of Mr. Ohlopkov to the new place of work were disagreements with the leadership of CENKI regarding the methods of completion of construction of structures and complexes of the cosmodrome, as well as methods of working with subcontractor organizations.
"It was decided that it would be better for everyone," says one of the top managers involved in the construction of the Eastern.
An employee of the government apparatus, in turn, calls the decision strange: "He was one of the best specialists, finding him an equivalent replacement will not be easy."
According to "Ъ", this will not be needed: the position of the technical director of the cosmodrome will be abolished, and its functions will be scattered by the units of the CENKI.
