The largest number – 717 illegal migrants were detained at the border with Moldova.
272 illegal migrants were detained at the EU border, most of them at the border with Slovakia, Poland, Hungary and Romania.
According to statistics, among the detained illegal migrants are mostly citizens of Moldova, Russia, Georgia, Turkey, Azerbaijan, Bangladesh, Vietnam, India and Armenia.
In addition, almost 2,000 potential illegal migrants were not missed into Ukraine.
The EU has found an unusual way to get rid of migrants.
Jazz in Skolkovo: experimentation and improvisation
The program of the second festival Skolkovo Jazz Science, which will take place on August 26 in the innovation center "Skolkovo", has been announced.
Guests are expected to perform by leading jazz groups and soloists, scientific discussions, interactive platforms and other musical and intellectual events.
As promised by the organizers, the site will become a territory of improvisation and a field for demonstration of new creative possibilities.
“The festival’s guests will be able to immerse themselves in the world of experimental media technologies and learn how innovation in science is becoming a new tool for interaction with art,” said Elena Zelentsova, Vice President of the Skolkovo Foundation.
Among the participants of Skolkovo Jazz Science 2017 a lot of stars, including the Moscow Jazz Orchestra of Igor Butman, who will present a joint program with vocalist Yaroslav Simonova.
Jazz and science are related concepts, and it is not by chance that they have come together, - explained the folk artist "Izvestia".
Experimentation and improvisation are appreciated by jazzmen as much as scientists.
One of the main events of the festival will be the performance of Azekel, a British of Nigerian origin, known for both his own work and his collaboration with the legendary Massive Attack and Gorillaz.
Jazz fans are looking forward to the performance of the five-time Grammy nominee, pianist Christian Sands (USA) with his trio.
In the new capacity will try one of the best academic chamber orchestras "Music Viva" under the leadership of Alexander Rudin and with the participation of the pianist Yuri Favorin.
The fusion of jazz, ethnic and electronic music, as well as academic traditions will be demonstrated by the ensemble "Marimba Plus" and its leader, composer and performer on marimba Lea Slepner.
One of the most unusual festival performances promises to become the set of the laureate of the award Sergey Kurehin Anton Muskeliadze.
The artist-experimentator controls music and video using gestures – this is how leap motion technology works.
A total of eight music groups will perform on the two stages of the festival.
In addition, the program includes open discussions, interactive areas and art objects united by the idea of merging music and science.
Guests will be able to participate in experiments, visit a scientific buffet and watch the creation of cryo-freezed or sturdy sand from starch and water.
In the special zone of vinyl you will be able to purchase recordings of current jazz performers and representatives of other musical directions, and at the book fair - publications on various topics, including musical, scientific and popular and biomedical literature.
