In Ukraine proposed to send Russians to prison for illegal crossing the border
The Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine has registered a draft law, according to which in the republic can appear criminal punishment for Russians for illegal crossing the Ukrainian border.
The document, registered in the electronic database of the Ukrainian parliament, entails a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens who attempt to illegally enter the country.
For repeated offences or acts committed by a group of persons, the term of imprisonment may be increased to five years.
If the offender was detained at the border with weapons, then the time of detention for him will increase to eight years.
Earlier it was that Ukrainian border guards detained Ukrainians who attempted to enter Russia outside the established checkpoints.
