In Russia will appear two new territories of advancing socio-economic development - "Abaza" and "Novotroitsk".
The relevant decrees of the Government of the Russian Federation will enter into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activities of the TOR are defined in the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khacasia.
In the city, where 15 thousand people live, special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, as well as the minimum amount of capital investments of residents, the minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investment in the city, and will also create more than 600 new jobs.
The list of types of economic activities in which Abaza will operate a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, for example, includes plant farming, livestock production, production of food products, non-alcoholic beverages and clothing.
The Government of the Republic has already signed framework agreements on the implementation of eight investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the city-forming enterprise of OOO "Abakan mine".
In January 2017, the authorities of the region that Khakassia fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the creation of TOR.
The authorities of the Orenburg region did the same.
There, in the city of Novotrojsk will also be created a territory of advanced socio-economic development.
This will allow to diversify the economy of the city, reduce its dependence on the urbanizing enterprise of Ural Steel JSC, as well as create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of economic activities in which a special legal regime for entrepreneurs will be applied in the new TOR includes, in particular, freshwater fisheries, feed production, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroitsk became the first of the Orenburg region monasteries to receive the status of TOR.
The territory of advancing development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investments and improve the life of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of the CIS can be distinguished as follows: income tax in the amount of not more than 5% during the first five years, and not less than 10% during the next 5 years, social contributions in the amount of 7.6% for 10 years, the use of the free customs zone regime, preferential connection to various infrastructure facilities, as well as preferential rates on rent.
